1
00:00:00,820 --> 00:00:03,050
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,050 --> 00:00:07,110
We've got trouble! Natsu's been trapped 
inside of an artificial dragon,

3
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:08,960
and is getting used as its power source!

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:11,110
Everyone wanted to try and rescue Natsu,

5
00:00:11,110 --> 00:00:14,440
but Magnolia's facing a crisis, 
too! What should we do?

6
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:16,970
Yes-yes-yes-yes-yes-yes-yes!

7
00:00:16,970 --> 00:00:19,990
The real show's just getting started, ya'll!

8
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,710
Bust this thing up, and me along with it!

9
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:58,260
But if we do that, what'll 
happen to you, Natsu?

10
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,320
Stop making excuses!

11
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,690
If Magnolia gets ruined 'cause of me,

12
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:05,350
I wouldn't be able to sleep at night!

13
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:09,420
Not budging a bit, huh?

14
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:11,050
At this rate...

15
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:13,080
...the city of Magnolia will be...

16
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:16,070
What should we do, Erza?

17
00:02:16,330 --> 00:02:18,630
Answer me, Erza!

18
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,590
Fairy Tail Wizards!

19
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:28,850
I heard a rumor while out on a job.

20
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:32,630
That someone was trying to 
make an artificial dragon...

21
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:35,120
That's how it started.

22
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,260
And you secretly met with this fool?

23
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:45,010
She said that she was gonna capture Natsu 
and use him as the dragon's power source.

24
00:02:45,010 --> 00:02:48,980
And during the meeting, I 
heard it was indestructible,

25
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:54,900
but for a dragon slayer's 
power from the inside.

26
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:57,170
I see.

27
00:02:57,170 --> 00:03:02,960
But if you hadn't handed Natsu over, that 
monstrosity wouldn't have been able to activate, yes?

28
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,830
No, that wasn't the only reason.

29
00:03:05,830 --> 00:03:10,370
Unless Natsu defeats her, the 
people in that city won't...

30
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:12,290
People in that city?

31
00:03:12,290 --> 00:03:16,840
That idiot went and forgot the promise he 
made to the people in the city without sound!

32
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:21,470
The guy just doesn't know when to quit.

33
00:03:21,790 --> 00:03:24,890
Sometimes I'd go see how 
he was doing out on jobs.

34
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:30,670
But that idiot forgets everything 
else when he's thinking about Igneel!

35
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:34,280
&#34;I'm not telling you to forget about Igneel,

36
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:39,110
but you must always remember your main role 
is that of a wizard of this guild.&#34; Yes?

37
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:43,650
I wasn't able to surpass Ul...

38
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,080
But him...

39
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:50,440
Natsu's the kind of guy 
who can surpass anything!

40
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:53,660
Even Igneel himself!

41
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:56,520
That's who Natsu is!

42
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:59,300
If he doesn't keep getting stronger...

43
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:02,300
Fighting him won't even be worth it!

44
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:04,990
Damn it...

45
00:04:05,830 --> 00:04:09,290
I thought he'd be able to destroy it easily.

46
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:12,680
Let me out there, Gramps.

47
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,480
Understood.

48
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:21,990
I'm going to give you the plan.

49
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:29,830
What incredible power!

50
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:32,120
This power is exquisite!

51
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,770
It's the same...

52
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,300
...as it was back then.

53
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:43,130
I saw it... I definitely saw it...

54
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,020
So fearsome...

55
00:04:55,020 --> 00:04:57,220
So ferocious...

56
00:04:57,220 --> 00:05:00,230
I'd never seen anything so beautiful.

57
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:05,300
But dragons are free spirits...

58
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:08,130
Since I never knew when 
I might meet one again...

59
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:11,240
I'd just make one myself!

60
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:15,730
Argh! Screw you!

61
00:05:15,730 --> 00:05:18,440
You ain't the only one 
that wants to see dragons!

62
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:21,990
So do I, and Wendy, and Gajeel!

63
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:23,520
But instead, you...

64
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,420
Dragons are gone.

65
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:27,180
They're extinct.

66
00:05:27,180 --> 00:05:28,930
Just a hallucination.

67
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:31,970
Liar, liar, liar!

68
00:05:31,970 --> 00:05:34,210
No one believed me.

69
00:05:34,210 --> 00:05:36,420
They laughed at me, ignored me...

70
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:40,490
Beings of such power, dragons...

71
00:05:40,490 --> 00:05:43,230
They kept denying they exist...

72
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:47,790
You must know how painful it is, yes?

73
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,770
Yes-yes!

74
00:05:49,770 --> 00:05:53,990
And now I've finally been able 
to unveil this! To show everyone!

75
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:56,820
Wow, that's some messed up backstory.

76
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:58,670
That's the reason?

77
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:01,130
First I'll crush this city,

78
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:03,580
and then fly around the entire continent!

79
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,470
Gray!

80
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:13,110
Sheesh... I should have seen this coming...

81
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:15,770
I'll give you the outlines 
of what really happened.

82
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:19,040
You're free to believe me or not.

83
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:25,330
Crap! I've got to at least stay conscious!

84
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:28,590
Come on, resisting any more 
is futile, I'm telling you!

85
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:31,050
It ain't futile! Put some guts into it!

86
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:33,450
Who's that?

87
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:36,550
Don't you get what Daphne is saying?

88
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:37,990
No, I don't!

89
00:06:37,990 --> 00:06:39,870
You forget about our promise?

90
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:41,480
Me?!

91
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,030
Only 6% left...

92
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,710
It's about time to start, I see.

93
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:47,880
Yes-yes-yes-yes!

94
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:51,170
H-He forgot?

95
00:06:51,170 --> 00:06:53,240
A promise as important as that?

96
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,860
Honestly! I'd expect that of him, but still!

97
00:06:56,860 --> 00:07:01,400
Thank goodness! Juvia 
believed in you, Gray-sama!

98
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,550
There wasn't any other method.

99
00:07:04,810 --> 00:07:08,940
But right now, our first priority is 
doing something about that big thing!

100
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:11,370
Do something? Like what?

101
00:07:11,820 --> 00:07:13,700
Someone's collapsed!

102
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,200
That's the owner of the cake shop!

103
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,700
He didn't evacuate fast enough!

104
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:17,560
Cover us!

105
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,540
We'll go save him!

106
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:23,000
Yes-yes! Lizardmen 3.1 show yourselves!

107
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,890
Crap! There ain't no end to 'em!

108
00:07:25,890 --> 00:07:28,250
What were you doing here?

109
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:31,000
My shop's been crushed...

110
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,330
But at least I saved this...

111
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:35,920
For this, you...

112
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:38,520
You were welcoming a newcomer, yes?

113
00:07:39,210 --> 00:07:42,540
I'm not going to lose to 
a big thing like that.

114
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:44,930
I'll heal him.

115
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:47,560
Hey, Wendy! Your magic power still hasn't...

116
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:50,240
Don't worry, I rested a little.

117
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,510
I'm counting on you, Wendy.

118
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,350
Right.

119
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,700
You know...

120
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,650
I can't stand pickled plums.

121
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:00,550
Pickled plums?

122
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:03,160
Yes... They're like, my weakness.

123
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:06,510
Everyone has one.

124
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:08,170
A weakness, that is.

125
00:08:08,650 --> 00:08:12,510
I've only just joined Fairy Tail.

126
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:15,180
I've only just started 
pretty much everything...

127
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:20,700
But I want to laugh more 
with Natsu, with everyone...

128
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,690
Cry with everyone, get mad with everyone...

129
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:27,700
I want to high-five Natsu-san once again!

130
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:33,340
Please, save Natsu-san...

131
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:34,800
Hey!

132
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:35,840
Wendy!

133
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,320
You fool! See what I said?

134
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:44,580
It's okay, she just lost consciousness.

135
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:47,190
But she's used up most of her magic power...

136
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:51,520
Only Natsu can defeat it.

137
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:55,880
But Master told us to attack the Dragonoid...

138
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:57,800
I see!

139
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,710
Erza, Gramps gave me a secret plan...

140
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,040
I figured as much.

141
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,340
You don't have to tell everyone.

142
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:09,140
The rest of you, eliminate the 
Lizardmen with everything you got!

143
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:11,440
I will take down the Dragonoid!

144
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,080
But, Erza...

145
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,860
What's gonna happen to Natsu?

146
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:19,070
This is the master's will, therefore 
it is Fairy Tail's will.

147
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:22,810
Got it? Protect this city, at all cost!

148
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:26,690
By the honor of our guild, our very soul!

149
00:09:26,690 --> 00:09:27,750
Erza...

150
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:32,500
I know... I'm a Fairy Tail 
wizard too, after all...

151
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,690
But...

152
00:09:33,690 --> 00:09:34,880
He-cat...

153
00:09:37,090 --> 00:09:39,230
Juvia, come with me.

154
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,060
Heaven's Wheel!

155
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,920
Blumenblatt!

156
00:09:45,310 --> 00:09:48,070
Yes-yes... Something that weak

157
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:49,440
is not a problem at all...

158
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:53,520
3% left until fully charged!

159
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,900
Where is it?

160
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,320
This thing's weak point... what is it?

161
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:01,870
Natsu...

162
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:08,470
I'm your friend... I have 
to save you, and yet...

163
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,200
Gray-sama?

164
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:15,330
Okay. This should be in 
that thing's blind spot.

165
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:18,170
The perfect place for a counterpunch.

166
00:10:18,170 --> 00:10:19,820
What exactly are you...

167
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:23,270
Juvia, I need your help.

168
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:27,230
This is the crucial moment to decide 
whether Natsu lives, or not.

169
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:33,220
I can't imagine a Fairy Tail without Natsu!

170
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,150
That just ain't happening!

171
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:37,610
Gray-sama!

172
00:10:38,610 --> 00:10:40,610
A Unison Raid.

173
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,120
Take this!

174
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:52,760
My magic power's about at its limit!

175
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:57,460
It's been bothering me for 
a while, but I'm sure now.

176
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:02,220
I've seen something like this before...

177
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,940
So loud!

178
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:17,590
Damn it! Destroy me!

179
00:11:17,590 --> 00:11:20,050
Or wait, I'm gonna destroy everything!

180
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:21,730
No, I'm not!

181
00:11:22,130 --> 00:11:24,290
It's acting odd...

182
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:26,240
This ain't good.

183
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:32,160
I can see it... That big thing's 
absorbing Natsu's soul!

184
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:35,510
Destroy me! I mean, I'll destroy!

185
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:37,800
I don't know anymore!

186
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,630
Natsu!

187
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:43,930
Out of my way!

188
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:48,830
See? Erza's all mad now.

189
00:11:48,830 --> 00:11:50,260
Yeah, I know!

190
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,110
We'll crush her, too!

191
00:11:52,110 --> 00:11:54,060
What are you sayin'? She's our friend.

192
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:56,940
Doesn't matter. Gonna crush her.

193
00:11:57,570 --> 00:11:59,040
I said shut up!

194
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,700
Stop arguing inside my head!

195
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:02,980
My, my...

196
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:05,480
I'm not sure why we can 
hear the whole thing...

197
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,700
W-What'll we do?

198
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:11,330
Even now, he must still 
be affected by Nirvana...

199
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:12,710
We're done with that already!

200
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:17,490
We're gonna cover for Erza, and 
crush all the grunts at once!

201
00:12:17,490 --> 00:12:18,500
But...

202
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:22,590
Ice and water... I felt it before 
when we faced each other,

203
00:12:22,590 --> 00:12:24,950
but I think our magic 
power is very compatible.

204
00:12:24,950 --> 00:12:26,090
Compatible?!

205
00:12:26,770 --> 00:12:30,100
As long as you believe in 
me, I'm sure we can do it!

206
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:32,790
Will you lend me your power, Juvia?

207
00:12:33,570 --> 00:12:34,670
Yes!

208
00:12:38,610 --> 00:12:40,600
Magic Power Fusion!

209
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:46,720
Unison Raid!

210
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:59,190
What the hell is this?

211
00:12:59,190 --> 00:13:00,590
A curtain of ice is...

212
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,390
The lizardmen are...

213
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:08,680
It's raining down icicles!

214
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:11,260
Whoa! That's cold!

215
00:13:14,230 --> 00:13:17,500
I know the feeling of this magic power!

216
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:19,900
It's a Unison Raid of water and ice!

217
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,640
Do you think Gray and Juvia...

218
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:24,880
They dddddddit it!

219
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,370
Wow!

220
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,920
Thanks, Juvia.

221
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:34,090
Juvia is glad.

222
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:38,200
Gray-sama puts it all on 
the line for his friends...

223
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,770
That's one reason I've come to l... l...

224
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:42,330
...love you!

225
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:45,920
Where'd Gray-sama go?!

226
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:49,400
Look at that! You gonna let him get away 
with stealing the juiciest scenes?!

227
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,310
Not bad, Gray.

228
00:13:51,310 --> 00:13:53,140
We should just crush that guy!

229
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:55,160
Shut the hell up!

230
00:13:55,810 --> 00:13:57,840
I'm gettin' so pissed right now!

231
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,670
Then why don't you crush this city, huh?

232
00:13:59,670 --> 00:14:00,940
I said I can't, okay?

233
00:14:02,230 --> 00:14:04,150
I think this is getting...

234
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:05,570
...pretty close to the edge.

235
00:14:05,570 --> 00:14:07,820
Can you hear me, Natsu?

236
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:08,970
Gray?!

237
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:11,410
You're completely helpless?

238
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:12,860
You should be ashamed!

239
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:15,810
You're nothing but talk, squinty eyes!

240
00:14:15,810 --> 00:14:19,900
How long are you gonna stayed fused in 
that thing, doing your one-man stand up?

241
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,630
What'd you say?!

242
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:24,420
What's that for? That's cruel, Gray.

243
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:29,630
You forgot about the promise you made!

244
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:32,420
And you still call yourself 
a Fairy Tail wizard?!

245
00:14:32,420 --> 00:14:35,880
Hurry up and destroy that dragon-thing!

246
00:14:37,770 --> 00:14:41,650
Yes-yes... So that's what you 
were after, Gray Fullbuster?

247
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:44,160
But it's already too late.

248
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:50,960
Why? Because Salamander's magic power, and 
even most of his will itself, has been absorbed.

249
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:53,410
If I could destroy this, 
I would've done it by now!

250
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:56,040
Go crush that droopy eyes flat!

251
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:58,570
I'm disappointed in you, Natsu!

252
00:14:58,570 --> 00:14:59,960
What?!

253
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:05,170
Isn't it so? Haven't you gotten through 
every challenge before by destroying stuff?

254
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:07,920
I don't wanna hear you say stuff 
like &#34;Bust me up with it&#34;!

255
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:13,090
That's right! Everyone... Everyone 
in Fairy Tail needs you!

256
00:15:13,090 --> 00:15:15,010
That's why we're trying so hard!

257
00:15:15,010 --> 00:15:18,970
A Natsu that doesn't respond to the feelings 
of his friends isn't the Natsu I know!

258
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:23,450
Lucy... Why, you...

259
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:24,730
That's so mean!

260
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:26,020
Let's crush her!

261
00:15:26,290 --> 00:15:27,950
Everyone's right!

262
00:15:27,950 --> 00:15:31,430
You're sitting there, trapped! 
You've completely given up!

263
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:33,340
When did I give up, exactly?!

264
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:34,300
Seriously though, give up.

265
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,870
No way, damn it!

266
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:38,130
You said &#34;bust me up&#34;, if I recall.

267
00:15:38,130 --> 00:15:40,080
That's the same as giving up!

268
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,580
It's nothing more than weakness!

269
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:48,090
So, just as you wish, I shall rid 
the world of this giant thing!

270
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:50,480
This has gotten kind of weird.

271
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:55,970
Whoa there... Natsu's soul has 
mostly fused with the Dragonoid!

272
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:01,140
Just try it!

273
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,330
Yes-yes-yes...

274
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:13,530
The Lizardmen might be wiped out, 
but as long as I have this power...

275
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:15,440
Whoa!

276
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:19,790
Fairy Tail has no need for those who 
view their own life as insignificant!

277
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,200
Say that again.

278
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:25,670
I can't imagine a prideful dragon ever 
wanting to see someone as weak-willed as you!

279
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:30,430
When you'd leap to his breast to 
embrace him, he would smack you silly!

280
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,220
Give me a break!

281
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:36,430
With this power, couldn't we beat Erza?

282
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:41,110
Sounds like fun! Bring it, Erza!

283
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:43,170
Today, finally, I will beat you!

284
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:45,770
Man, what a simpleton.

285
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:49,940
I can hear it! He is pretty much 
saying exactly what he feels!

286
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:51,070
Yes!

287
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:52,990
We're doing impressions, <i>now</i>?!

288
00:16:52,990 --> 00:16:56,450
Oh? Hey, don't move on your own!

289
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:59,700
You scared, Erza?

290
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:02,540
Someone like you...

291
00:17:05,140 --> 00:17:07,790
Nope, she's scary after all!

292
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,420
It's not enough...

293
00:17:10,420 --> 00:17:12,800
What, that all you got?

294
00:17:15,090 --> 00:17:19,030
I ain't kiddin' around here!

295
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:20,040
Uh-oh!

296
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,820
The magic power being absorbed 
is exceeding capacity!

297
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:24,180
What happened all of a sudden?

298
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:30,100
All you guys think you can get 
away with pushin' my buttons?!

299
00:17:31,370 --> 00:17:33,360
The flames of emotion.

300
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:35,110
Natsu!

301
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:37,000
Natsu-san...

302
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,610
Man, this is messed up.

303
00:17:39,610 --> 00:17:43,160
I warned him and everything, you know.

304
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:48,370
Now the guy who's always hot under the 
collar has a body that's hot all over!

305
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,100
Gajeel!

306
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:53,250
Man, the dolt.

307
00:17:53,250 --> 00:17:54,840
Gajeel?!

308
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,010
Stop makin' work for me!

309
00:17:57,010 --> 00:17:58,980
Secret Dragon Slayer Art!

310
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:01,600
Karma Demon: Iron God Sword!

311
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:12,660
Gajeel...

312
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:16,600
Looks like I still got a ways to go.

313
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:21,570
I was tryin' to pulverize the entire 
thing and bust you up with it.

314
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,090
Oh, you...

315
00:18:25,370 --> 00:18:28,460
Lucy! Call that horse guy!

316
00:18:28,460 --> 00:18:31,500
Send all the fire ya got on an arrow in here!

317
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,090
Nice, Gajeel!

318
00:18:33,090 --> 00:18:34,890
Leave it to me!

319
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,960
As it were, moshimoshi!

320
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:41,930
Can everyone hear me? Anyone 
who can use fire, lend a hand!

321
00:18:42,180 --> 00:18:43,230
Okay, got it!

322
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:43,990
Oui!

323
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:45,910
We just need to send fire to Natsu, right?

324
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:47,040
Let's go, Al!

325
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:47,880
Yeah!

326
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,190
I can do it, too!

327
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:53,230
Thrust fire into that breast 
until he can eat no more!

328
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:55,280
We're counting on you, Sagittarius!

329
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,750
Moshimoshi!

330
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,770
Truce! I call truce!

331
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:01,610
It can't absorb any more magic power!

332
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:05,940
That stupid woman's insulted the 
pride and majesty of dragons.

333
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:08,180
Don't hold back. Crush her good.

334
00:19:08,570 --> 00:19:10,160
Don't have to tell me twice.

335
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,080
Now! Fire!

336
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,360
All on one shot!

337
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,000
Moshimoshi!

338
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:18,420
Solid Script! Heat Spell!

339
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:21,880
Requip, Big Bazooka!

340
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:21,840
Guns Magic, Blast Bullet!

341
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:23,140
Oui!

342
00:19:23,140 --> 00:19:24,780
Explosion!

343
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:27,760
Natsu, I'll pay back my debt!

344
00:19:32,230 --> 00:19:34,440
Take it, Natsu!

345
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:52,960
Now that I've eaten, I'm all revved up!

346
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:58,040
I'm fired up!

347
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:04,460
Anger! That, itself, is the 
source of his greatest power.

348
00:20:04,460 --> 00:20:05,760
Master...

349
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:10,410
Freeing himself, and 
standing up to adversity...

350
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:13,250
It's the motivational power 
he needed to break through it.

351
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:17,230
The best way was to make Natsu angry.

352
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,220
Figures!

353
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:20,530
We all thought the same!

354
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,950
I told Gray to make Natsu angry.

355
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:28,660
And it looks like Erza figured it 
out without me saying anything.

356
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:31,840
Everyone, take a good look!

357
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:36,350
A Fairy Tail wizard is 
ridding this city of evil!

358
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:40,630
Okay, you dragon-crazed freak! 
You've really pissed me off now!

359
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:46,900
Go ahead, try and use one of 
those &#34;Hidden&#34; techniques...

360
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,590
I'm gettin' more power all the time here...

361
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:53,650
More than you can hide from with your magic!

362
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:00,730
I finally... met one...

363
00:21:00,730 --> 00:21:03,030
Apologize to Igneel!

364
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:05,870
For this impostor dragon!

365
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:15,780
Daphne's curse has been lifted!

366
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:18,000
Did he keep his promise?

367
00:21:18,260 --> 00:21:20,920
That Fairy Tail wizard!

368
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:24,570
You see that, Igneel?

369
00:21:24,570 --> 00:21:27,920
In the end, the weak 
point of the Dragonoid...

370
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,690
...was the source of its 
power, Natsu, himself.

371
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,900
Seems like it!

372
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:36,620
Gray! You really did it this time!

373
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:39,410
It was your fault in the first place!

374
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:44,180
No matter how much we fight, 
no matter what happens,

375
00:21:44,180 --> 00:21:48,450
all of us at Fairy Tail need each other.

376
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:52,620
We can't lose even one, you know?

377
00:21:53,210 --> 00:21:56,170
Everyone is looking for someone,

378
00:21:56,170 --> 00:21:58,580
and everyone responds to that.

379
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:05,000
And that's while I'll say 
it again: I love Fairy Tail!

380
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,910
Hey, Lucy...

381
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:08,880
What?

382
00:22:09,260 --> 00:22:13,680
When you smile, don't people 
say you look like a sunfish?

383
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:18,300
What the heck?! No, nobody says that!

384
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:21,430
You <i>sure</i>?

385
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:59,470
Natsu, tomorrow's finally the 
annual cherry blossom viewing!

386
00:23:59,470 --> 00:24:02,510
Right! But I need to finish 
up a request first.

387
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:05,370
I gotta get Wendy used to work quick, see.

388
00:24:05,370 --> 00:24:07,500
Natsu, Gray, Erza...

389
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:10,740
I'm worried you guys are going to 
have a negative influence on Wendy.

390
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:13,420
Uh, can you put a little 
more trust in us, please?

391
00:24:13,890 --> 00:24:16,460
Next time: Rainbow Sakura!

392
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:20,380
I think her choice of teachers 
was a fundamental mistake.

393
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:22,300
Then who'd be better?

394
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,910
Maybe... Freed?

395
00:24:24,910 --> 00:24:27,130


